releases.name: v2.0.11
releases.body:
### Upgrade Warning!

 We introduced a fix for Windows, that impacts everyone who upgrades. Storjshare-GUI will now create a new folder in the path you specify. To migrate anything prior to `storjshare-gui@2.0.11`, delete everything in the `storjshare-<drive_id>` folder, and place the old `contracts.db` and `sharedata.kfs` folders inside the new `storjshare-<drive_id>` folder.

### Issues Closed
- Closes #405
- Closes #404

releases.body:
Improved system tray information. The system tray icon is now always visible and close will only close the gui but it will still run in the system tray. Menu quit or system tray menu quit will close the system tray process.
- Better OS specific event handling 
- Various bug fixes

releases.name: v0.6.0(beta)
releases.body:
## Changelog
- DriveShare renamed to StorjFarmer
- Remove dependency on dataserv-client
- Integrate with storj/core
- Now farms real data on the Storj network
- Seeds the Storj Bridge API (api.storj.io)
- Optional telemetry reporting for test group payouts 
  - Built in bandwidth tester
  - Please leave enabled during beta to help us improve the network and receive rewards

> NB: New settings and configuration file - you must reconfigure your drives.

## Screenshots

releases.name: Multi-Drive Support and Rewrite
releases.body:
Rewrite of the GUI with multi-drive support and better usability. Add more drives to your payout address. Driveshare-GUI will do the magic in the background for you.

We changed the color of the start and running button. If the button is green, everything is running fine. We added some error messages for different failure situations.

![screenshot 0 4 1](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6333390/11693425/17617500-9ea5-11e5-9988-5e7ae555c934.jpg)

releases.name: Multiplatform Support
releases.body:
The setup module was updated to support Mac, Windows, and Linux (tested with Ubuntu 32 bit). This is an alpha build, there might still be issues. Please [post an issue](https://github.com/Storj/driveshare-gui/issues) if you run into problems and please attach a screenshot with the logs window open (click View Logs).

We're working on adding multi-drive functionality, by running multiple instances of dataserv-client at one time. Stay tuned!

![Mac Build](https://slack-files.com/files-tmb/T02GWQ23X-F0E8KKL07-f10c879307/driveshare_720.png)

releases.name: Improved logging during setup errors
releases.body:
Some users are reporting issues during setup, so I'm adding some logging to help track down the issue.

Mac binary is now available, but is in pre-alpha state and might have issues. Please try it out though, we'd love to get your feedback on it.

releases.name: Minor Bug Fix: Invalid Directory on Windows
releases.body:
Fixed an issue that caused the free space label to always display "Invalid Directory" on Windows.

Only providing Windows binaries for now since auto-setup isn't yet implemented in Mac and Linux. However, driveshare-gui can be installed with git and node on Mac and Linux. See the [README](https://github.com/Storj/driveshare-gui/blob/master/README.md) for more info.

NOTE: There is an issue with showing the amount of free space on Windows. A solution is being worked on.

releases.name: DriveShare Windows 32bit
releases.body:
All executables were built using Python 2.7.

# Windows
- This was not build with an .ico so the icon may look better (comparable to the OSX build) in future builds.
- Immediately apparent bug is that the used-storage-bar and the percentage indicator does not initialize correctly on this build. (edit: This is now known to be an issue with running the app in Python 2.7. It not only happens once packaged).

## Windows spec file

```
from kivy.tools.packaging.pyinstaller_hooks import install_hooks
install_hooks(globals())
# -*- mode: python -*-
a = Analysis(['..\\ds-source\\DriveShare_GUI.py'],
             pathex=['C:\\Users\\MetaFeta\\Desktop\\Kivy-1.8.0-py2.7-win32\\PyInstaller-2.1\\dsw'],
             hiddenimports=[],
             runtime_hooks=None)
pyz = PYZ(a.pure)
exe = EXE(pyz,
          a.scripts,
          exclude_binaries=True,
          name='dsw.exe',
          debug=False,
          strip=None,
          upx=True,
          console=False )
coll = COLLECT(exe, Tree('../ds-source/'),
               a.binaries,
               a.zipfiles,
               a.datas,
               strip=None,
               upx=True,
               name='dsw')
```

# OSX

The associated app will only run on OSX 10.6.x or greater. Tested on OSX 10.10.

## OSX spec file (10.6+)

```
# -*- mode: python -*-
from kivy.tools.packaging.pyinstaller_hooks import install_hooks
install_hooks(globals())
a = Analysis(['../storj/driveshare-gui/DriveShare_GUI.py'],
             pathex=['<PATH TO PYINSTALLER>/pyinstaller/DriveShare'],
             hiddenimports=[],
             runtime_hooks=None)
pyz = PYZ(a.pure)
exe = EXE(pyz,
          a.scripts,
          exclude_binaries=True,
          name='DriveShare',
          debug=False,
          strip=None,
          upx=True,
          console=False )
coll = COLLECT(exe, Tree('../storj/driveshare-gui/'),
               a.binaries,
               a.zipfiles,
               a.datas,
               strip=None,
               upx=True,
               name='DriveShare')
app = BUNDLE(coll,
             name='DriveShare.app',
             icon=None)
```
